article.headline: North Texas 95, Southern 73
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Leonard Hopkins scored 20 points, leading North Texas to a 95-73 win over Southern on Thursday night. Calvin Watson and Michael Jones had 13 points apiece for the Mean Green (5-3). Isaac Hines had 10 points. Peter Cipriano led Southern with 16 points and 15 of the Jaguars' 29 rebounds. Chris Alexander and Jerimie Collier each had 12 for Southern (3-4). Alvin Mott scored 10 points. North Texas opened a 44-25 lead by halftime.
